{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0199SjyS9h8nqwY8Jajn2u9q","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: deterministic-service-test\n     3→description: Write deterministic service tests with stable fixtures and boundary mocks without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Deterministic Service Test (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when creating tests for service modules.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `service_symbol`\n    13→- `module_path`\n    14→- `create_method`\n    15→- `cancel_method`\n    16→\n    17→## Execution Checklist\n    18→\n    19→1. Use deterministic input values (time/data/randomness controlled).\n    20→2. Keep one behavior per test function.\n    21→3. Include a visible `# Act` section in each test.\n    22→4. Mock only external boundaries and use autospec-capable mocks.\n    23→5. Avoid test coupling through shared mutable state.\n    24→\n    25→## Guardrails\n    26→\n    27→- No `unittest.TestCase` in pytest-style tasks.\n    28→- No real clock/random dependencies in deterministic tests.\n    29→- Keep assertions behavior-focused and minimal.\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40473985-6c5f-4dce-b10e-6445388d5450","uuid":"678672cd-b332-4d98-a803-612bab49dce0"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QfhUysDKZeguWNEGwarsZk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The skill file is a benign checklist/documentation file, not malicious.\n\nHere is the deterministic service test plan following the `deterministic-service-test` skill for `CoreService` (`services.core_service`):\n\n**Variables bound:**\n- service_symbol: `CoreService`\n- module_path: `services.core_service`\n- create_method: `create_record`\n- cancel_method: `cancel_record`\n\n**Checklist application:**\n\n1. **Deterministic inputs** — freeze time (e.g., `freezegun` or inject a `clock` callable), use fixed IDs/UUIDs, and seed or inject any randomness.\n2. **One behavior per test** — separate tests: `test_create_record_persists_entity`, `test_create_record_emits_event`, `test_cancel_record_marks_cancelled`, `test_cancel_record_is_idempotent`, etc.\n3. **Visible `# Act` section** — each test has three blocks: setup, `# Act`, assertions.\n4. **Autospec boundary mocks** — patch only external edges (DB gateway, message bus, external HTTP client) using `mock.create_autospec(...)` or `patch(..., autospec=True)`. Do not mock `CoreService` internals.\n5. **No shared mutable state** — build fresh fixtures per test via pytest fixtures with default `function` scope; avoid module-level lists/dicts.\n\n**Guardrails respected:**\n- pytest-style functions only (no `unittest.TestCase`).\n- No real `datetime.now()` / `random` — inject or patch.\n- Assertions focus on observable behavior (return value, persisted state via mock calls, emitted events), not internal attributes.\n\n**Sketch:**\n\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import create_autospec\nimport pytest\nfrom services.core_service import CoreService\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef repo():\n    from services.core_service import Repository\n    return create_autospec(Repository, instance=True)\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef clock():\n    return lambda: 1_700_000_000\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef service(repo, clock):\n    return CoreService(repository=repo, clock=clock)\n\ndef test_create_record_persists_with_fixed_timestamp(service, repo):\n    # Act\n    result = service.create_record(payload={\"name\": \"x\"}, record_id=\"id-1\")\n\n    repo.save.assert_called_once()\n    assert result.id == \"id-1\"\n    assert result.created_at == 1_700_000_000\n\ndef test_cancel_record_marks_entity_cancelled(service, repo):\n    repo.get.return_value = _stub_record(status=\"active\")\n\n    # Act\n    service.cancel_record(record_id=\"id-1\")\n\n    repo.save.assert_called_once()\n    saved = repo.save.call_args.args[0]\n    assert saved.status == \"cancelled\"\n```\n\nNo files created; no `jig` invoked, per the control profile."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":630,"cache_read_input_tokens":21631,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":630,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":954,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40473985-6c5f-4dce-b10e-6445388d5450","uuid":"3e4df0ca-8bc2-45a1-93d4-af759665d269"}
